But since these series always converge to real numbers (because of what is called the completeness property of the real numbers), to talk about the series in this way is the same as to talk about the numbers for which they stand. In particular, the decimal expansion 0.111… can be identified with /. This leads to an argument that , which only relies on the fact that the limit laws for series preserve the arithmetic operations; this argument is presented in the article 0.999...





